    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">1. Duolingo: Best for Habit Building</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Duolingo remains the king of consistency. Its gamified approach, with streaks and leaderboards, makes learning feel like a daily ritual. The lessons are short, making it perfect for busy learners who only have five minutes to spare.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">While it lacks deep grammar explanations, it is an excellent tool for building a core vocabulary and staying motivated. The free version is highly functional, making it accessible to everyone.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">2. Babbel: Best for Practical Conversation</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Babbel focuses on real-world scenarios. Each lesson is built around a specific topic, like ordering coffee or asking for directions. It explains the grammar rules behind the sentences, helping you understand how English actually works.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">If you want to feel confident speaking in practical situations, Babbel is a strong choice. It requires a subscription, but the structured path is worth the investment for serious learners.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">3. Busuu: Best for Structured Learning</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Busuu offers a comprehensive, level-based curriculum (A1 to C2). One of its best features is the community feedback, where native speakers correct your writing and speaking exercises. This human touch makes a big difference in your progress.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">The lessons are professionally designed and follow a logical progression. It is a great middle ground between a casual app and a formal course.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">4. ELSA Speak: Best for Pronunciation</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">If your goal is to reduce your accent and sound more natural, ELSA Speak is the leader. It uses advanced AI to analyze your speech and provide instant feedback on your word stress and intonation.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">The app is highly specialized. It will not teach you much grammar, but it is the best companion for anyone who wants to perfect their American or British accent.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">5. Rosetta Stone: Best for Immersion</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Rosetta Stone uses an immersive method with no translations. You learn by matching images with words and phrases, much like a child learns their first language. This method helps you think in English from day one.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">It is a slower, more meditative approach compared to the fast-paced games of Duolingo. It is best for learners who want a deep, natural connection with the language.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">6. Cake: Best for Learning from Real Content</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Cake uses short clips from movies, TV shows, and YouTube to teach English. You listen to how people actually speak in real life, not just in a textbook. It is a fun, modern way to improve your listening and learn current idioms.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">The app is free to use and highly engaging. It is an excellent supplement to a more structured course or app.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">7. Lingodeer: Best for Grammar Clarity</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Lingodeer provides some of the clearest grammar explanations of any app. It breaks down complex rules into simple, easy-to-understand notes before you start the exercises. This makes it a favorite for learners who like to know the "why" behind the language.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">The lessons are well-organized and the audio quality is excellent. It is a solid, reliable choice for building a strong foundation.</p>

